I am building a Spring Boot backend and a Next.js frontend for my professional portfolio at caseycapozzi.com.

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: Next.js (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- Backend: Java Spring Boot with Lombok, hosted on AWS ECS
- Styling: Always use Tailwind CSS — never inline styles or CSS modules unless absolutely necessary
- Icons: lucide-react (preferred), react-icons as secondary

## API
- Production: https://api.caseycapozzi.com
- Local dev: http://localhost:8080
- Next.js dev server: http://localhost:3000
- API calls from the browser go through Next.js proxy routes (`/api/status`, `/api/docs`) to avoid CORS

## React / Next.js Conventions
- Prefer server components for pages that do not need state or browser APIs
- Add `"use client"` only when a component uses hooks, event handlers, or browser APIs
- Always use named exports for components (not default exports) — except for Next.js page files, which must use default exports
- New components go in `app/components/`
- New pages go in `app/<route>/page.tsx`

## Java Conventions
- Always use Lombok (`@Data`, `@Builder`, `@RequiredArgsConstructor`, etc.) — never write boilerplate getters/setters
- Use constructor injection (not field injection) in Spring beans

## Key Files
- `app/layout.tsx` — shared layout with Navigation and Footer
- `app/components/Navigation.tsx` — floating pill nav (icons + labels, active route state)
- `app/components/Footer.tsx` — footer with AWS status line
- `app/components/LiveAwsCoreStatus.tsx` — polls `/api/status` and shows online/offline
- `app/api/status/route.ts` — server-side proxy to the Spring Boot `/api/v1/status` endpoint
- `app/api/docs/route.ts` — server-side redirect to Swagger UI
